
@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Odisha";
}
<link href="~/Script/StatesCss/odisha.css" rel="stylesheet" />
<div class="main-container">
    <!-- BACKGROUND IMAGE -->
    <div id="top-section-main">

        <div id="top-section-content">
            <h1> Bhubaneshwar </h1>
            <h2> Odisha </h2>
        </div>
    </div>
    <!-- PLACES TO VISIT SECTION -->
    <div id="feature-section">
        <h1 class="feature-section-title"> The top places to visit in <i>Odisha</i></h1>
        <div class="feature-content">
            <div class="cols-3">
                <img src="~/Image/StateImage/Odisha/puri.jpg">
                <h3> Puri </h3>
                <p> One of the most sacred pilgrimage sites for Hindus, Puri also known as Jagannath Puri, is located in the state of Odisha. </p>
            </div>
            <div class="cols-3">
                <img src="~/Image/StateImage/Odisha/cuttack.jpg">
                <h3> Cuttack </h3>
                <p> Cuttack is known as the Millennium City as well as the Silver City due to its history of 1000 years and famous silver filigree works. </p>
            </div>
            <div class="cols-3">
                <img src="~/Image/StateImage/Odisha/sambalpur.jpg">
                <h3> Sambalpur </h3>
                <p> Sambalpur is famous for its Hand loom textile works, popularly known as Sambalpuri Textile. </p>
            </div>
            <div class="cols-3">
                <img src="~/Image/StateImage/Odisha/rourkela.jpg">
                <h3> Rourkela </h3>
                <p> The city is also popularly known as Ispat Nagar and also as the Steel City of Odisha. It has one of the largest steel plants of the Steel Authority of India Limited (SAIL) known as Rourkela Steel Plant.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <!-- MAP SECTION -->
    <div id="showcase1-container">
        <div class="showcase">
            <div class="cols-2">
                <iframe class="showcase1-pic" src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3834854.698229437!2d82.19066081926452!3d20.176754265618815!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x3a226aece9af3bfd%3A0x133625caa9cea81f!2sOdisha!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sin!4v1618327165589!5m2!1sen!2sin" width="600" height="450" style="border:0;" allowfullscreen="" loading="lazy"></iframe>
            </div>
            <div class="cols-2">
                <div class="feature-text">
                    <h1 class="section-title">
                        Facts of Odisha
                    </h1>
                    <p class="section-content">
                        <ul class="section-content-list">
                            <li>
                                Hirakud in Odisha is the longest man-made dam in the world.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Odisha police pigeon service started on an experimental basis in 1946 to deliver messages to remote areas of the state.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Odisha hosts India Surf Festival at Ramachandi Beach in Puri every year.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                The Chandipur Beach of Balasore is famously nicknamed as the “hide and seek beach”. This is because during low tide, the water recedes up to 5 kilometres every day only to return during the high tides.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Every year, the city of Bargarh and the adjoining areas turn into the largest open-air-theatre, known as the Dhanu Jatra.
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <!-- LAST SECTION -->
    <div id="call-to-action">
        <div class="showcase">
            <div class="cols-1">
                <h1 class="action-title" style="color:black;">
                    What are you waiting for??
                </h1>
                <p style="line-height:1.2em; margin-top:-100px; color:black;">
                    Book your tickets, pack your bags and
                    Get.. Set.. GO!!
                    Fond of ancient temples and traditional cultures, then Odisha is definitely waiting for you!!
                </p>
                <P>
                    <a href="#" class="BookHotelBtn"> BOOK A HOTEL TODAY!! </a>
                </P>
                <div class="text"> <p style="font-weight:1000; font-style:italic; color:black; margin-top:-70px;"> Talasari Beach - Odisha </p></div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

